cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.LG 

The paper discusses attribute-based access control (ABAC) policy mining algorithm, which involves data analysis, machine learning, and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves database-related concepts such as access control lists (ACL) and role-based access control (RBAC), which suggests cs.DB (Databases). The algorithm used in the paper involves generalization and simplification of candidate rules, which is a machine learning technique, indicating cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves software engineering concepts such as policy development and migration, suggesting cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves quality selection of candidate rules, which is a statistical learning technique, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning).
